{
  "stem": "23090.5",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And this poor man could not-- when I say poor man, he was the home guard.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And because the young guys in the camps were always run by the-- by the SS, or somebody like that.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "But they were SS who were either injured, or they lost a leg, or an arm, or an eye.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And since they could no longer be on the front line, their reward, or whatever it was, was to make them camp commanders.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And they were very, very angry.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "They were very obviously angry people by losing one of their limbs, and so on.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "So I can tell you that they were not nice guys, and they didn't-- did their job beautifully.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "But this guy was an old guy, and so he had to guard us.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "We'd leave the camp like about 6:00 in the morning, and we had to go through all these corn fields.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "It seemed like it was kilometers after kilometers, until we got to the kitchen.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "And when we got to the kitchen, we peeled all these things, and this guy had to march us all the way back in the evening.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "And he would sit all day long, kibbutz with the Germans while we were peeling potatoes all day long, and cabbage, and so on.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And this went on for about two or three weeks.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And, finally, the last kid in the end, he would say he kind of liked us, you know, because what else could he do?",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And he couldn't schlep his rifle anymore, he couldn't drag this, because it was just a load on him.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So he would take off the minute we got into these corn fields, in this area that was not visible.",
      "word_count": 20
    }
  ],
